ProtoDefines:
. "For $0\leq n\leq m$, the $n$th \term{convergent} of the 
   continued fraction $[a_0,\ldots,a_m]$ is $[a_0,\ldots, 
   a_n]$. These convergents for $n<m$ are also called \term{ 
   partial convergents} ."
